comments.body:
Its relying on this fold: https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/blob/88f041f3e05e26617856cc096d2e2864dfaa1c7b/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCasts.cpp#L819-L825

Which later folds down to the icmp_slt - but fails on this issue due to the multiple uses of `%.lobit`

A similar direct fold would work though:
```cpp
    if (match(Src, m_LShr(m_Value(X), m_SpecificInt(SrcWidth - 1)))) {
      // trunc (lshr X, BW-1) to i1 --> icmp slt X, 0
      return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, X, Zero);
    }
```

or even:
```cpp
    if (match(Src, m_AShr(m_Value(X), m_SpecificInt(SrcWidth - 1))) ||
        match(Src, m_LShr(m_Value(X), m_SpecificInt(SrcWidth - 1)))) {
      // trunc (ashr X, BW-1) to i1 --> icmp slt X, 0
      // trunc (lshr X, BW-1) to i1 --> icmp slt X, 0
      return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, X, Zero);
    }
```
